<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFJeremy_Reimer">Jeremy Reimer (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2008-03-16"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="03-16"><a href="/wiki/March_16" title="March 16">March 16</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2008" title="2008">2008</a></span>). <a href="http://arstechnica.com/articles/paedia/past-present-future-file-systems.ars" class="external text" title="http://arstechnica.com/articles/paedia/past-present-future-file-systems.ars" rel="nofollow">"From BFS to ZFS: past, present, and future of file systems"</a>. arstechnica.com<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://arstechnica.com/articles/paedia/past-present-future-file-systems.ars" class="external free" title="http://arstechnica.com/articles/paedia/past-present-future-file-systems.ars" rel="nofollow">http://arstechnica.com/articles/paedia/past-present-future-file-systems.ars</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-03-18</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=From+BFS+to+ZFS%3A+past%2C+present%2C+and+future+of+file+systems&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Jeremy+Reimer&amp;rft.au=Jeremy+Reimer&amp;rft.date=%5B%5BMarch+16%5D%5D%2C+%5B%5B2008%5D%5D&amp;rft.pub=arstechnica.com&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Farstechnica.com%2Farticles%2Fpaedia%2Fpast-present-future-file-systems.ars&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:File_system"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
